    },
    {
      "content": "Yeah, so typically all of our guys most of the time gate here around 7:35 in the morning and they'll get the trucks ready get, you know, all set up for the day they leave the yard around 8:00 in our box truck. Most of the time. It's going to be just two guys you in the lead sometimes depending on the job size. We may have 3456 guys but most of the time will be two guys and essentially you get the customers at around 8:30. You all loaded up, drive unload and be done with the day. Most of the time. Guys are back around 4:00 to six in the afternoon. I'd say about eighty percent of the time but we are going to have times when you may be back a little bit earlier or you may be out later till 78910 PM those longer days usually come, you know, unexpected day, day of we try to make sure we plan support it and get everybody out at a good time but there are either, could be days where you may be required to be out that late. So it does need some flexibility on your end. If you know full-time employees usually get your forty hours in about four days right now, I'm trying to work on like a four day schedule you're like working four days on one day, on-call those on-call days you know if we need you last minute. If we had a call out or a crew support we'll call you in last minute. You'll get paid $5 additional per hour for coming in.",
