      "content": "But, yeah, generally the job itself. I mean you have a little bit of experience with movie you know you're not stuck behind a desk job or get to be out about room Houston, sometimes we have out of town moves to Austin, Stin Dallas, San antonio, but you get to explore, I mean you get to see different lifestyles connect with different people. It's not like a retail job where you talked to a hundred different customers. You know you focus on one customer to a day and really get to know them. They get to know you, so, it's fun in that aspect of you social person, you know, you wanna build some report starting pay.",
